This paper deals with edge detection and recovery in images, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of active contour models, which falls under the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics). Additionally, the paper uses gradient vector flow, which is a common technique in image processing and falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves the use of local continuity and smoothness cues, which can be considered as a form of machine learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves the use of snakelets, which is a specific type of active contour model, and this falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
